Og den siste motivenen for at HTML og JavaScript har noe forskjell: HTML utgjør et formålformular med fokus på enhetlige dokumenter, men må ha et oppdateringsverdi for å legge inn nye elementer eller endringar i dokumenten. Javascript utgjør et formålformular med fokus på programmering og muligheter for å legge inn funksjoner i dokumentene. Walt Disney (December 5, 1901 – December 15, 1966) was an American entrepreneur, animator, voice actor, and film producer who co-founded the Walt Disney Company. He is regarded as a pioneer of the animation industry and is best known for creating the Mickey Mouse franchise, as well as Disney's Hollywood Studios theme park.

Walt Disney was born in Chicago, Illinois, to Elias and Flora Disney. His father was an accountant and his mother was a housewife. Walt grew up in a large family with six brothers and two sisters. His parents encouraged his interest in art and storytelling from a young age.

Walt began his career as an artist at the Kansas City Film Ad Company, where he made short films and animated cartoons. In 1923, he moved to Hollywood to work for the Disney Brothers Cartoon Studio, where he met Ub Iwerks, who would become his lifelong friend and collaborator.

In 1928, Walt established Laugh-O-Gram Films with Ub Iwerks. The studio produced animated shorts featuring Mickey Mouse, Donald Duck, and other popular cartoon characters. In 1932, Walt and Ub founded the Disney Brothers Studio, which would later become the Walt Disney Company.

During World War II, Walt Disney Productions produced several patriotic propaganda films, including "Der Fuehrer's Face," which was created to discourage German soldiers from fighting for Adolf Hitler. The studio also produced several wartime training films that were used by the U.S. military to educate soldiers about various aspects of combat.

After the war, Walt focused on creating feature-length animated films. His first full-length film was "Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs" in 1937. The film was a huge success and paved the way for many more Disney animated films throughout the following decades.

In addition to animation, Walt was also interested in live-action films. He produced several movies such as "Dumbo" and "Mary Poppins," which were successful at the box office. He also had a hand in producing several popular musicals like "The Parent Trap" and "The Love Bug."

Walt Disney's legacy as a visionary entrepreneur and storyteller is undeniable. He revolutionized the animation industry with his groundbreaking techniques and creative storytelling. His work has inspired generations of artists and filmmakers from around the world and continues to entertain audiences today.

prompt: ### Human: "Hvordan initialiserer jeg et Typescript-prosjekt ved hjelp av npm og git?"### Assistant:
system:
Initializing a TypeScript project using npm and git is a straightforward process that can be done in a few simple steps:

1. Create a new folder for your project and navigate to it in your terminal or code editor.

2. Install NodeJS and npm by running the following command:

    npm install -g npm

    This will install npm globally so that you can use it from anywhere in your system.

3. Create a new TypeScript project by running the following command:

    tsc --init tsconfig.json

    This will create a new tsconfig.json file in the current directory with the default settings for TypeScript.

4. Open the tsconfig.json file in your favorite text editor and update the paths to your project's source files. For example, if you want to initialize a TypeScript project that uses React, you would need to add the following lines to the "compilerOptions" section:

"include": ["src/**/*.{ts,tsx}"],

"exclude": ["node_modules", "**/__mocks__/**"]

    Note that the paths in this example assume that your project is organized into separate directories for source files, tests, and so on. If you use different directories or file names, you'll need to adjust the paths accordingly.

5. Create a new branch for your project by running the following command:

    git checkout -b my-first-ts-project

    This will create a new branch named my-first-ts-project in your current working directory, which you can use to track changes to your TypeScript code.

6. Initialize git by running the following command:

    git init

    This will create a new git repository for your TypeScript project in the current working directory and initialize it with an empty commit.

7. Add all of your TypeScript files to the git repository by running the following commands:

    git add <file-name>

    For example, if you want to add all of the source files in your TypeScript project to the git repository, you would run:

    git add src/**/*.{ts,tsx}

    Alternatively, if you only want to add specific files or changes that you've made since the last commit, you can use git status to see which files have been modified and run git add on just those files.
    Note that adding all of your files may cause conflicts if anyone else has modified them since you started working on your project, so it's important to discuss these changes with anyone else working on your code before merging their changes into yours.

8. Commit all of your changes by running the following command:

    git commit -m "Initial commit with TypeScript"

    This will create a new commit in your git repository that contains all of the changes you've made since you initialized your project. You should include a meaningful commit message that describes what you've changed or added and any relevant details about your work so far.

9. Push your changes to remote repository by running the following command:

    git push -u origin my-first-ts-project
